last_episode_to_air.name: The Hunt for Lost Gold
last_episode_to_air.overview: Elementary my dear Angus!. A couple of Sherlock Holmes fans sell silverware, costumes and books after a flood hit their homes. Plus will army swords score big at auction?

name: The Yorkshire Auction House
overview: Observational documentary series following auctioneer Angus Ashworth and his staff throughout the process from house viewings to auction day as they travel around the UK looking for antiques and collectables to sell.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Auctioneer Angus Ashworth has been running his auction house for more than a decade. With the help of his team and family, he clears out cluttered homes, uncovering hidden gems that he can sell at auction.

episodes.name: Cumbria Farmhouse
episodes.overview: Angus and the team clear out a farmhouse in Cumbria, where they uncover some wonderful antiques, including a box of collectable toy cars and a 19th-century bureau.

episodes.name: Sutton Coldfield Collection
episodes.overview: Angus is in Sutton Coldfield to look through a collection, uncovering Beatles memorabilia and two programmes from England's 1966 World Cup win.

episodes.name: Shropshire Big House
episodes.overview: Angus and the team clear out a big house in Whixall, Shropshire, uncovering a Victorian desk set, a hanging lantern and Vogue clothing patterns.

episodes.name: Newcastle House Clearance
episodes.overview: Angus is in Newcastle to clear out a home full of books, and takes an interest in a Bechstein piano, a scary vase and a silver loving cup.

episodes.name: Scottish Attic Clearance
episodes.overview: Angus and the team clear out an attic that is filled with Ferrari memorabilia and take the collection to auction to see how much it makes.

episodes.name: Filey Couple
episodes.overview: The team helps a couple clear out their home in the seaside town of Filey, and Angus sees potential in some vintage toys and boxes of old soap.

episodes.name: Derbyshire Widow
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth and the team are in Derbyshire to help a widow clear out her home, where they uncover a riding crop, a 19th-century stool and a jewellery collection.

episodes.name: Aviation Collection
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth and the team clear out a huge aviation collection in Co Durham, then help a retired policeman sell items from his four-bedroom home.

episodes.name: Fife Clutter
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth and the team are in Fife to dig through three generations of family clutter, uncovering a rocking horse and a collection of rare Beatrix Potter figurines.

episodes.name: Coventry Historic House
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth and the team search for interesting items at a historic home in Coventry, then travel to Aberdeenshire to collect some unusual Asian furniture. Last in the series.

episodes.name: Boynton Telephone Collection
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth travels to the small village of Boynton in East Yorkshire to clear out a collection of vintage telephones, and helps a family sort through 50 years of clutter.

episodes.name: Stockton-on-Tees House Clearance
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth is asked to help with an emotional house clearance in Stockton-on-Tees, and is invited to examine the work of two semi-professional artists.

episodes.name: episode 3
episodes.overview: A recently retired woman wants to declutter her home and raise some money to help pay to visit her family abroad, so Angus Ashworth travels to Horsforth to dig through her collection.

episodes.name: episode 4
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth and the team are in Harrogate to look through an impressive art deco collection. They then travel to Shropshire to hunt for some hidden gems among the items at a cottage.

episodes.name: episode 5
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth heads to Bradford to look through a vast collection of coins, toys and jewellery. Plus, the team clear some Yorkshire-made furniture from a beautiful cottage.

episodes.name: episode 6
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth and his team face the mammoth task of clearing a collection of bow top caravans. Plus, a widower wants to sell a collection of stamps and Beatrix Potter figurines

episodes.name: episode 7
episodes.overview: After clearing out a home in Leeds, the team sorts through a van full of mysterious boxes. Meanwhile, Angus Ashworth checks out a retired archaeologist's beautiful collection.

episodes.name: episode 8
episodes.overview: In Knaresborough, North Yorkshire, Angus and the team sort through a massive collection of model aircraft and paintings. He also sells at auction some iconic children's toys.

episodes.name: episode 9
episodes.overview: Angus and the team clear out the home of a retired couple who own an impressive collection of Ladderax furniture. Later, Angus sees potential in some commemorative

episodes.name: episode 10
episodes.overview: The second series concludes with Angus travelling to Warwickshire where he is excited to clear out a historic house in Long Itchington. Each room is full of interesting items, including vintage furniture and some precious jewellery.

episodes.name: The Road to Riches, By Bus or By Bike
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth helps a Sheffield family find a new home for a collection of motorbikes left by their much-missed husband and dad.

episodes.name: Family Treasure Funds a New Home
episodes.overview: Stuart hopes Angus Ashworth can help him raise enough money to adapt a house for his ill wife's needs, so she can live her final years in comfort.

episodes.name: Missing Jewels and Mysterious Artwork
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth helps Amanda and Steve clear their late parents' home in Huddersfield, which is full to the brim with memories and treasured possessions.

episodes.name: Hong Kong to a Galaxy Far Away
episodes.overview: A man asks Angus Ashworth to clear his late father's home, which is packed with unusual items from East Asia, but some forgotten toys are the stars at auction.

episodes.name: A Shedload of Silver
episodes.overview: A huge haul of silver leaves Angus Ashworth speechless and raises a staggering amount at auction, while later Angus helps Susan clear a huge collection of railway memorabilia.

episodes.name: Home-Made Treasure Trove Surprise
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth struggles to value Victor's homemade curios, but gets a surprise at auction and he also searches for treasures in an eclectic collection.

episodes.name: A Pink Poodle and a Potato Picker
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth visits a home packed with weird and wonderful collectables. Then, he is called back to see a previous client to clear an attic and garden.

episodes.name: A Very Local Job
episodes.overview: Angus travels to Wetherby in West Yorkshire to meet John and Anne. After recently taking a tumble from a tree which injured his arm, John has decided to clear out his quirky collection of antiques.

episodes.name: From Memories to New Beginnings
episodes.overview: Brenda asks Angus Ashworth to find new homes for her jewellery collection, but it is her son's childhood toys that might make big money on auction day.

episodes.name: A Lost Masterpiece?
episodes.overview: Angus spies a treasure while helping a couple to downsize and he then turns detective to try and identify whether a work of art is by a very famous artist or not.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Auctioneer Angus Ashworth has been running his auction house for more than a decade. With the help of his team and family, he clears out cluttered homes, uncovering hidden gems that he can sell at auction.

episodes.name: Huge Bids for a Rare Collection
episodes.overview: Angus uncovers a loft stashed with bizarre but highly valuable collectables. Plus, a set of rare stamps deliver a big cash windfall at auction.

episodes.name: Animal Rescue and the Gold Haul
episodes.overview: A charity needs cash to feed rescued animals, so Angus tries to help them raise a sizable sum. A widow discovers her late husband's collection is worth a fortune.

episodes.name: Watches, Lighters & Ceramic Horses
episodes.overview: Angus clears a garage packed to the brim with rare antiques. Later, he meets a woman and her collection of valuable ceramic horses.

episodes.name: Barber's Collection Makes the Cut
episodes.overview: Angus uncovers a rare coin collection and some vintage hair cutting gear. An old sea chest proves to be a treasure trove at auction.

episodes.name: Ringing Bells and a Rare Watch
episodes.overview: Angus helps a grieving daughter clear her late mum's huge collection of bells. Another job sees a room emptied for the first time in 50 years.

episodes.name: Three Generations of Heirlooms
episodes.overview: A cancer survivor calls on Angus to sell family heirlooms to fund an around the world trip. Elsewhere, a coin collection makes a mint at auction.

episodes.name: Fishing Reels and Garden Trains
episodes.overview: Angus helps to clear a warehouse filled with collectables to fund a luxury holiday. Plus, a pensioner sells his huge model railway.

episodes.name: Rare Radios and a Jukebox
episodes.overview: Angus finds a valuable part of a Lancaster Bomber in a widow's home.

episodes.name: Machinery Mementos
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth helps two National Health Service workers sell 30 years' worth of collectables in Oxford. Later, he discovers over 200 crane replicas.

episodes.name: A Victorian Bonanza
episodes.overview: Angus Ashworth takes a trip back in time when he visits a home that is dressed like a Victorian townhouse. Later, he helps a mother and daughter with an emotional task.

episodes.name: Old Master and Model Maker
episodes.overview: Angus discovers a mysterious 17th century artwork in Scotland. Then, he heads to Peterborough to help clear the home of a keen model maker.

episodes.name: Toys, Toys, Teddys and Dolls
episodes.overview: Angus takes a trip down memory lane as two cherished childhood collections go under his gavel. For one customer, it’s a very emotional time.

episodes.name: To Be Cherished By Others
episodes.overview: Angus attempts to find new homes for the beloved belongings of a departed father. Then, he helps a widow clear her late-husband's collection.

episodes.name: Time to Let Go
episodes.overview: Angus finds thousands of comics that's one man's obsession, but his wife wants them gone. A man's poor health forces him to give up his passion for timepieces.

episodes.name: The Gold Disc and the Golf Pro
episodes.overview: For the first time at the auction house, Angus puts a gold disc under the gavel, before selling off memorabilia from a former Ryder Cup referee.

episodes.name: Grease Is The Word
episodes.overview: Angus and Jack clear one man's enormous personal collection of vintage oil cans. Plus, a former pub landlord sends a barrel-load of goodies to auction.

episodes.name: The Rock N Roll Auctioneer
episodes.overview: An iconic Gibson guitar goes under the gavel. Plus, a huge haul of classic rock vinyl triggers an avalanche of ferocious bidding.

episodes.name: Quantity Versus Quality
episodes.overview: In Timperley, Angus encounters a 4000-piece collection of royal memorabilia. Plus in Wakefield, he finds some valuable 19th century Chinese porcelain.

episodes.name: Strange, Old, Big and Small
episodes.overview: Angus discovers Morris Minor cars and African carvings. Later, he finds Harrod's sheepskin coats from the 1960s and mysterious stone objects

episodes.name: Failure Not An Option
episodes.overview: Angus must pull out all the stops to sell two cherished collections, one of which was kick started by a horrific, near-fatal accident

episodes.name: A Little Lady Makes Big Money
episodes.overview: As the documentary series returns for a fourth series, Angus Ashworth finds a rare porcelain figure that is worth big money. A widow gets a nice surprise when her late husband's collection sells for a small fortune.

episodes.name: Ancient Antiquities
episodes.overview: Angus unearths some ancient Greek and Roman artefacts in Derbyshire. In Kent, Angus is attracted to a curiously well-travelled wardrobe.

episodes.name: Toying with a Life Down-Under
episodes.overview: Angus unearths a treasure trove of toys in Manchester. Plus, three generations of heirlooms go under the gavel, but is their owner ready to sell?

episodes.name: Can Toy Cars Get Us to the Arctic?
episodes.overview: A retired couple asks Angus to sell their toy collection. Will they make enough funds to fulfill their dream of seeing the Northern Lights?

episodes.name: Two Hundred Clocks & One Rare Vase
episodes.overview: Angus helps an engineer and his wife with their collection of 200 clocks. Plus, will a rare vase help a couple fulfill their dreams?

episodes.name: Sign of True Love Goes to
episodes.overview: Angus unearths a collection of quirky scientific instruments. Plus, a father sells family keepsakes to fund his daughter's university studies.

episodes.name: Yorkshire Greatest Showman
episodes.overview:
Angus discovered fairground items and a 1920s Ford Model T.

And helps a man clear the once- treasures possessions of his late parents.

episodes.name: Brotherly Love And Kitsch Cats
episodes.overview: Angus helps a man sell his sibling's rare books and toys. Plus, a cruise ship singer wants to downsize her kitsch collection of mid-century ornaments.

episodes.name: The Animals Sold Two by Two
episodes.overview: Angus helps clear a menagerie of animal-themed heirlooms. Plus, a couple wants to raise money to take their disabled son on a holiday of a lifetime.

episodes.name: Who Dares Wins at Auction
episodes.overview: A collectable Piggy Bank called Wesley goes under Angus's gavel. Plus, a family wants to sell rare SAS badges belonging to a fallen warrior relative.

episodes.name: A Hoard Of Hidden Coins
episodes.overview: Childhood toys and a coin collection need to be sold to pay for a widow's home costs, and a downsize means some risqué art needs to go under the hammer.

episodes.name: A Rootin'-Tootin' Auction
episodes.overview: Angus needs to sell some wild west costumes. And a widower's unfashionable furniture needs to make big money so he can be reunited with his family.

episodes.name: A High Spirits Hoard
episodes.overview: A cancer survivor wants to sell his beloved whisky collection for a good cause. And a huge decorative pot is the surprise draw on auction day.

episodes.name: Norwegian Silver
episodes.overview: Angus helps a lady part with her late husband's cherished medals. And a well-travelled woman sells her quirky items to fund a trip of a lifetime.

episodes.name: Angus Pulls a Cracker
episodes.overview: Angus uncovers an unopened bottle of 1940s whisky and some Victorian Christmas crackers. At auction it's chocks away for an old cabin crew uniform.

episodes.name: From Russia with Love
episodes.overview: A widow returns from Italy, bringing with her some Soviet propaganda. While some Victorian gadgets sees Angus geek-out over technology from a bygones age.

episodes.name: Selling Up Before Baby Comes
episodes.overview: With just a month before her due date, Gem and Tom ask Angus to visit their 16th century Suffolk home. Plus, a retired couple needs help with a downsize.

episodes.name: The UK's Biggest Collection
episodes.overview: A couple with a collection of dishes asks Angus to sell them to fund a trip to Australia. Plus, Angus finds a huge fire engine part in a living room.

episodes.name: Yorkshire Mice and Russian Dolls
episodes.overview: Cancer survivor Claire wants to downsize to free up some cash and have fun, and Clive needs funding for his mum's care home costs.

episodes.name: Dad's Valuable Hoard
episodes.overview: Angus battles a huge clearance and discovers an ancient warriors helmet.

episodes.name: Copper Kettle Cupid
episodes.overview: Angus visits a house packed to the rafters with vintage copper. Then he helps a couple clear their home before they relocate to Thailand.

episodes.name: A Gold Medal & A Hand Grenade
episodes.overview: A surprise find in a client's garden has Angus's team stunned, but will a big silver key unlock a generous donation to a worthy charity?

episodes.name: Yorkshire's Greatest Showman
episodes.overview: Angus receives a call from two sisters desperate to find new homes for their late father's incredible collection of circus memorabilia.

episodes.name: A Rare Bear and a German Cat
episodes.overview: A customer needs Angus' help to thin out the items inherited from her father. Plus, two brothers learn the worth of their late father's eclectic hoard.

episodes.name: The Hunt for Lost Gold
episodes.overview: Elementary my dear Angus!. A couple of Sherlock Holmes fans sell silverware, costumes and books after a flood hit their homes. Plus will army swords score big at auction?
